lars to discuss a variety of issues representing the strengths of Courtney's work. Topics explored include: the transformation of Canadian parties, the impact of party leaders on the electoral fortunes of their parties, new avenues for public involvement in the policy-making process, Royal Commissions, opinion polls, access to information, the malaise of Canadian democracy, institutional reform, and indigenous nationalism.Timely and engaging, this impressive collection honours an important scholar and makes a valuable contribution to the field.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aPolitical leadershipzCanada. 0aPolitical participationzCanada. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aBlais, André, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCairns, Alan C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarty, R.K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClercy, Cristine De, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDion, Stéphane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerguson, Peter A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGidengil, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarchildon, Gregory P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMichelmann, Hans J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMichelmann, Hans J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPerlin, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSeidle, F. Leslie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSteeves, Jeffrey S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStory, Donald C., eeditor.4edt4http: